               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Säʿatat za-lelit wa-za-nagh “Horologium for the Night and the Morning
                     Hours” (fols. 3r-56r) 
 I-1) Introductory prayers and hymns (fols.
                     3r-14r)
 - Halle luya… ʾaʿattǝb wa-ʾǝtnäśśaʿ ba-sǝmä ʾab… “Hallelujah… I
                     make the sign of the cross and stand up in the name of the Father…”
                     (Introductory prayer) (fols. 3r-4v)
 - Gǝnäyu la-ʾǝgziʾabǝḥer… “Serve the
                     Lord…” (Hymn to God) (fols. 4v-5v)
 - Rǝḫuqä mäʾat… “Far from anger…”
                     (Prayer) (fols. 5v-6v) 
 - ʾƎweddǝsäkki ʾo-dǝngǝl… “I praise You, o
                     Virgin…” (Hymn to St Mary) (fols. 6v-7r) 
 - Täzäkkär ʾǝgziʾo kidāna…
                     “Remember, O Lord, the covenant…” (Hymn to the Lord) (fols. 7r-8r) 
 - Nǝʿi
                     ḫabeyä ʾo-dǝngǝl… “Come to me, O Virgin…” (Hymn to St Mary) (fols. 8r-9v)
                     - Nǝsebb[ǝḥo] la-ʾǝgziʾabǝḥer… “We praise the Lord…” (Praise of God) (fols.
                     9v-11r) 
 - Gänäynä la-ki ʾo-walatta Dāwit… “We have served You, O daughter
                     of Dāwit…” (Hymn to St Mary) (fols. 11r-11v)
 - Sǝʾalu la-nä… “Pray for
                     us…” (Hymn to the saints and angels) (fols. 11v-14r).
 I-2) Readings (fols.
                     14r-17r)
 - for Monday (fols. 14r-16v) 
 - for Sunday (fols. 16v-17r)
                     
 I-3) Principal prayers and hymns (fols. 17r-56r) 
 - Kʷǝllomu
                     śarāwita malāʾǝkt manfasāwǝyān… “All hosts of the spiritual angels… ” (Hymn to
                     God) (fols. 17r-19v) 
 - Mogäs wa-kǝbrǝnä qärnä mädḫanitǝnä... “Grace and
                     our glory, the horn of our salvation…” (Hymn to the Trinity) (fols.
                     19v-25v)
 - Salām la-ki Māryām la-Noḫ ḥa[mä]ru… “Salutation to You Mary,
                     Noah’s Ark… ” (Hymn to St Mary) (fols. 25v-30v) 
 - Tafaśśǝḥi Māryām Fāsikā
                     la-ʾAddam… “Rejoice, Mary, Adam’s Easter…” (fols. 30v-36r)
 - Taʿabbǝyo
                     nafsǝya la-ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer. Saʾāli lana Māryām… “My soul extolls God. Pray for us
                     Mary…” (Prayer to St Mary)  (fols.
                     36r-41r)
 - Säʾal la-nä Giyorgis näʿa näʿa näʿa näʿa Giyorgis… “Pray for us
                     George; come, come, come, come George… ” (Hymn to the saints, angels, etc.)
                      (fols.
                     41r-44v)
 - Mäḥarännä ʾAb. Hale luya. Täśahalännä Wald. Hale luya Manfas
                     Qǝddus… “Have compassion upon us, Father. Hallelujah. Have mercy upon us, Son.
                     Hallelujah Holy Spirit…” (Prayer to the Trinity) (fols. 44v-45v)
 -
                     Täśahalkä ʾǝgziʿo… “You had mercy, o Lord…” (Prayer to God) (fols.
                     45v-46v)
 - Tafaśśǝḥi ʾo-Māryām mǝlǝʾtä ṣaggā… “Rejoice, o Mary, full of
                     grace…” (Hymn to St Mary) (fols. 46v-47r)
 - ʾO-rǝḫrǝḫta ḫǝllinā… “O
                     tender-hearted...” (Hymn to St Mary) (fols. 47r-48r) 
 - Salām la-sǝʾlǝki
                     za-yǝʾeddǝm la-nǝṣṣare… “Salutation to Your icon which is pleasant to the
                     sight…” (Greeting to the Icon of the Virgin Mary) (fols. 48r-50v)
 - Hale
                     luya nǝsgǝd la-ʾabä bǝrhānāt… “Hallelujah, let us worship the Lord of the
                     lights...” (fols. 50v-53r) 
 - ʾƎsebbǝḥ ṣaggāki ʾo-mǝlǝʾtä ṣaggā... “I
                     praise Your grace, o full of grace…” (Hymn to St Mary) (fols. 53r-54v) 
 -
                     Kʷǝllomu śarāwita mälaʿǝktä manfasāwǝyān… “All hosts of the spiritual angels…”
                     (Hymn to St Mary) (fols. 55r-56r)
 
 Additiones 1-3.</summary>
