                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">f. 1v</locus>
                           <desc>: Hymn to St Mary.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: [እ]ሴብህ፡ ጸጋኪ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: I praise Your grace...</quote>
                           <note> Hymn from the “Säʿatat”. Written in a recent hand (in dark crimson
                              ink), incomplete. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>: Hymn to St Mary.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: ተፈሲሒ፡ ማርያም፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: Rejoice, Mary...</quote>
                           <note> Hymn from the “Säʿatat”. Crudely written in pencil, incomplete.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>: Hymn to St Mary.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>: ኩሎሙ፡ ሠራዊተ፡ መላእክት፡ መንፈሳውያን፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>: All hosts of the spiritual
                              angels…</quote> Written in a recent hand, incomplete. The same hymn
                           has been started to be written on <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>
                           <note> (above Additio 2). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The word ድንግል፡ (“Virgin”) is written (in black ink, by
                           the scribe) in the upper margin of <locus target="#47v">47v</locus>; the
                           word በከመ፡ (“Like, as”) is written upside down (in black ink, by the
                           scribe) in the bottom margin of <locus target="#48v">48v</locus>.
 -
                           Several names are written in red ink in the same hand as the main text on
                              <locus target="#56r">56r</locus>, at the end of the text: [ወለ]ተ፡ ተክለ፡
                           ሃይማኖት፡ [ገብ]ረ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም።, [Wälä]ttä Takla Hāymānot, [G]äbrä
                           Takla Hāymānot, Walda Māryām.
 - A note mentioning the title ውእቱ፡
                           ሰአታት፡ ዘቤተ፡ ክርስትያን፡ “This is the Hours of the church”, and a personal name
                           in Latin script, Kahsay, are written (recently; in pencil) on <locus target="#57r">57r</locus>.
 - The title of the work (ሠአታት) is
                           written in pen in the upper margin of <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.
 - A simple black line is used as text divider on <locus target="#50v">50v</locus> and 56r.
 - Corrections (words or
                           letters) are written interlineally and in the margins: <locus target="#14v">14v</locus>, 54v.
 - Immediate corrections indicated
                           by thin lines above and below the word: <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>,
                           48r.
 - Erasures: <locus target="#8r">8r</locus>, 10r.
 - Crude
                           minor notes: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 19v, 20v, 22r, 23r, 25v,
                           26r, 29r, 30v, 33v, 34r, 57v.
 - Crude drawing on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- For the readings of Monday and Sunday, the
                              indications of the days have been wrongly inverted as follows: for
                              Monday ዘዘእሑድ፡ (abbreviated in ዘዘሐ፡), for Sunday ዘዘሰኑይ፡ (ዘዘሰኑ፡) (s.
                              fols. 14r and 16v). the references to specific hours are not given and
                              the title is not mentioned.</desc>
                        </item>
